latestIgtvVideos.title: Stay Safe everyone 😷
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There’s no new life changing information in this video, but sometimes it hits different coming from people you trust and I guess I’m hoping to make that here. These are dark days, and our nation in particular is only headed towards darker ones. Stay indoors, stay safe and make sure people around you do the same. Try and change the perspective of those who are still taking this time very lightly. I know friends who’re struggling to find hospital beds for their loved ones. We’re losing people and the nation is running low on resources. Try and help out as much as you can, and keep yourself and all the others near you safe. Even if it doesn’t tuen out to be deadly for you, it can be for others around you. Remember that! If you’re to step out, I’d advice to wear surgical masks instead of the cloth ones. 
Hoping for better and healthier days for all🙏
-

Two years. 730 days. One wild, beautiful, chaotic, love-filled ride. 💫
We’re officially 2 years old today! Who would’ve thought that your one trip to New York would take you off the market forever, and hand you the best passenger princess for life. 💍
From chaos to quiet coffee mornings, from fights over laundry to holding hands through every high and low—this life thing with you feels like home (and a rom-com with bloopers 😂). 
No marriage is perfect. People aren’t either. But somehow, we’ve made a little magic out of all our flaws, laughs, quirks, and tantrums. And honestly? I wouldn’t trade it for anything.
You are the best decision I’ve ever made. Thank you for being my biggest adventure, softest landing, and everyday love story. ❤️
Here’s to us- imperfectly perfect, forever-ish kind of love. ✨
Happy 2nd, my forever human. Love you a lil too much.
-
#2YearsMarried #AnniversaryFeels #happyanniversary #adventureseveryday
